{"word":"ἀγριαίνω","slug":"ἀγριαίνω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀγριαίνω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἄγριος'><el>ἄγριος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> <i>to be angered, provoked, chafed</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <el>τινί</el> <i>with</i> one, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> of rivers, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>Causal, <i>to make angry</i>: <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be angered</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}